channel.title: HELP! Can't log into my server(any source) can sum1 help?
channel.description: ive posted this many times, but no1 gives good information. When i run my server, it wont let me on, with any source, usualy i can get on once, but like when i compile it or run it twice, it wont let me on. I see other people on cuz i see them typing commands, but i can never get on, when i click log in it says on runserver liltwixis11 is loggin in, blahblahblah it doesnt say im rejected or banned or n e thing like that, it says what it says for everyone else, but i can never log in. At first i thought it was a problem with my source (Fr33Sc4p3 Pkz), but i used other sources(phone, pimp, mine, p16, ect) none of them worked either, it all was the same, showed up on runserver. but i couldnt get in. If someone knows how to fix it, can you tell me pleeeaasee? P.S: Ill rep++ you if you help me fix it =]

item.title: HELP! Can't log into my server(any source) can sum1 help?
item.dc:creator: @liltwixis11 liltwixis11
item.description:
@liltwixis11 wrote:

[quote=“Zenzie, post:23, topic:81890”][quote author=Public Void link=topic=120332.msg1189145#msg1189145 date=1177136590]
Lol, from the picture above that is totally wrong. The port is usually 43594 or 5555 (unless you changed it), and the IP is wrong, that is the default IP. You might want to use Hamachi (if you do use the IP at the top of your hamachi page after making a Hamachi Network) or you might want to use No-Ip (you need port forwarding). You might want to use Mod Taharoks Compiler that works also.
[/quote]

Dont be a noob that wants to be the wiseguy …

Picture is correct it hasnt have to be 43594 or 555
IP is not wrong its the localhost
And his compiler works fine[/quote]

True dat, i have a no-ip, that worked, and im not a nub junior member like u public void, who probably doesnt even know wut a public void is ;), so does n e 1 know how i can fix it?
